# Privacy Policy

**Effective Date:** July 10, 2025  
**App Name:** ApiaryAI  
**Developer:** Daniel Najda Pty Ltd  
**Contact:** danielnajda@danielnajda.com

This Privacy Policy describes how ApiaryAI ("we", "us", or "our") collects, uses, and protects your information when you use our mobile application.

---

## 1. Information We Collect

We collect the following types of information:
- **Location Data:** To tag apiary sites and hive locations.
- **Media Access:** Photos and audio recordings stored locally or in cloud storage.
- **Account Information:** We collect login credentials for authentication purposes.
- **Analytics:** We use Google Analytics to understand how users interact with the app.
- **Device Information:** Basic metadata like device type and OS for bug reporting and analytics.

---

## 2. How We Use Your Information

We use the information we collect to:
- Store inspection records and related media
- Track apiary site locations
- Authenticate user access to the app
- Improve app performance and stability
- Analyze feature usage and user behavior for improvements

---

## 3. Data Sharing

We do **not sell** or rent your personal data.  
We only share data with trusted service providers used to operate and maintain the app:
- **Firebase** (data storage & authentication)
- **RevenueCat** (purchase processing)
- **Google Analytics** (anonymous usage tracking)

---

## 4. Data Storage & Security

We store your data securely using Firebase and encrypted transmission protocols.  
However, no system is 100% secure. You are responsible for exporting or backing up your own inspection data regularly.

---

## 5. Your Rights

You may:
- Request to access or delete your account and associated data
- Opt out of analytics tracking (device-level)
- Contact us at danielnajda@danielnajda.com with any privacy-related concerns

---

## 6. Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy at any time. Changes will be posted within the app or on our official GitHub policy page.

---

